If Quick Summoning stack with Casting Deftness,<br>
then QS lv2(25% haste) plus CD lv2(15% haste) plus Focus ring(15% haste),I can save 3 AA and having same summoning haste(50%), and I can have 15% haste for casting other non summoning spell, if they are stackable.<br>
Moreover, Casting Deftness working on our nukes too, it should be much better then just train Quick Summoning lv3.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2389<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 4:36:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=446.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can Quick Summoning stack with Casting Deftness ?</span><hr size=1> I had not considered Casting Deftness, but I strongly suspect that only one of CD or QS would take precedence, whichever had the highest percentage, and that they would not add.  Otherwise, QS3 at 9 AA would be a complete waste of points, and it was not during the era of old transvergence.<br>
<br>
It <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">does</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> add with focus effects though.<br>
<br>
I have 14 AA banked.  I think 2 points CD1 might well be worth it, and then I will be able to report whether it stacks or not.<br>
<br>
WAIT:  The key word here in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Alternate_Advancement_Skills/Spell_Casting_Deftness.htm">Spell Casting Deftness</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>beneficial</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  None of our summons are beneficial, and very few of our spells are beneficial.<br>
<br>
Ask <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Rhion</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for a precise definition of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;beneficial,&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he will be more than glad to give it to you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
